DTO Files

1.post dto -->remove id and unit,created by ,createdon,lastmodifiedby,lastmodified on 

2.update dto-->remove createdon,created by

3.child for all dto not required -->createdon,created by,lastmodifiedby,lastmodified on ,unit

4.inside child update and post dto --> remove id

5.

i)In model we need to check all names,datatypes(ex:Number(bto,po,do,odo -->string),
Qty(decimal(13,3)),price(decimal(18,3))).inital letter should be caps..
uoc and uom should be string in model as well as dtos..

ii)we need to give proper requred field for all model and dto compare with our new tips UI link(http://syn.wyzmindz.com:4504/sales/lp-release)

6.we need to check both all models and all dtos(post,update,getdto) field should be match...

7.In dbcontext files you need to mention all the models include child model..

8.model name should be meaningfull and camelcase for all dtos and models... 

9.In mapping file we need to given meaningfull name end with dto 
(CreateMap<BinningLocation, BinningLocationDto>().ReverseMap();)
 and in dto(post,update,get) child class
meaning full name like (public List<BinningLocationPostDto>? BinningLocationPostDto { get; set; })

10.In program file we need to check the repository is mentioned or not and also check repositoryname

11.in repository create method we need to given unit name above the create();

12.in repository varaible name, method name,result message should be meaning full/camelcase and properly use 
await and asyn keys...

13.in repository in getallmethod need to give order by decanding order in where condition (OrderByDescending(x=>x.Id))

14.In IRepository method name,parameter name and data type should be meaningfull....

15.in controller methodname,varaible name ,error message,passing responce properly,in return you need to pass service responce....







